The paper proposes a method for learning a similarity kernel and using it for clustering, which are topics related to machine learning and data mining. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.DM (Data Mining) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of random projection forests, which are a type of decision tree, indicating a possible connection to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of the rpfCluster algorithm for clustering, which involves the use of leaf nodes, indicating a possible connection to cs.CV (Computer Vision) or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
